# Operational Documentation

- Update the nearest operational README when testsuite, finalise, fixerrors, release metadata, or command behavior changes.
- Document safety confirmations, destructive behavior, recovery commands, and generated artifact paths.
- Never place passwords, service keys, auth state, production payloads, or private report content in tracked documentation.
- Keep `docs_private/release-log.md` as the only tracked file under `docs_private/`.
- Use FFTS repository-relative paths and commands.

